
Various external tools are used by the toolkit. If you want to use them, please find them and respect their license.

============================================================

colea
http://ecs.utdallas.edu/loizou/speech/colea.htm


COLEA: A Matlab Software Tool for Speech Analysis 
by Philip Loizou


The MATLAB program is distributed as freeware and is intended 
for non-commercial purposes only.


============================================================

columbia_ee_dtw 
http://www.ee.columbia.edu/ln/labrosa/matlab/dtw/


Dynamic Time Warp (DTW) in Matlab by Dan Ellis


If you find this code useful and wish to reference it in your 
publications, you can make a reference directly to this web 
page, e.g. something like:

D. Ellis (2003). Dynamic Time Warp (DTW) in Matlab
    Web resource, available: 
http://www.ee.columbia.edu/~dpwe/resources/matlab/dtw/.

The code originated with our project on aligning MIDI 
descriptions to music audio recordings,

R. Turetsky and D. Ellis (2003): Ground-Truth Transcriptions of 
Real Music from Force-Aligned MIDI Syntheses,
4th International Symposium on Music Information Retrieval 
ISMIR-03, pp. 135-141, Baltimore, October 2003.

Copyright

This software is released under GPL. See the COPYRIGHT file.
Last updated: $Date: 2012/09/05 10:19:14 $

  
